SMS Spam Classifier App

A complete SMS Spam Classification System using Python, Machine Learning, FastAPI, and Streamlit. This project covers data preprocessing, EDA, ML model training, API creation, and interactive frontend.

Features & Steps Implemented ⿡ Data Preparation & Cleaning

Loaded dataset spam.csv with columns label (ham/spam) and message.

Checked dataset shape, columns, missing values, and duplicates.

Removed unnecessary columns (Unnamed: 2,3,4) and duplicate rows.

Result: Cleaned dataset with no missing values or duplicates.

⿢ Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)

Frequency counts of labels (ham vs spam).

Calculated characters, words, sentences per message.

Statistical summary for all data, separately for ham and spam.

Visualizations:

Pie chart for label distribution

Histograms for number of characters and words by label

Pairplot for feature correlations

Correlation heatmap

WordCloud of all preprocessed messages

⿣ Text Preprocessing

Convert text to lowercase

Tokenization into words

Remove special characters & punctuation

Remove stopwords (NLTK)

Stemming using PorterStemmer

Rejoined tokens to create final_message for ML

⿤ Machine Learning Model

Algorithm: Multinomial Naive Bayes

Text converted to numeric using TF-IDF

Split: 80% training, 20% testing, stratified

Hyperparameter tuning using GridSearchCV for alpha values [0.01, 0.05, 0.1, 0.2, 0.5, 1.0]

Saved best model and vectorizer with MLflow & Joblib

Results:

Best Parameters: {'nb__alpha': 0.1} Accuracy: 0.9729206963249516

Classification Report: precision recall f1-score support

       0       0.98      0.99      0.98       903
       1       0.95      0.83      0.89       131

accuracy                           0.97      1034
macro avg 0.96 0.91 0.94 1034 weighted avg 0.97 0.97 0.97 1034

Confusion Matrix: [[897 6] [ 22 109]]

⿥ FastAPI Backend

Created FastAPI app with /predict POST endpoint

Input: JSON with "message": "text here"

Output: JSON with "label" (Ham/Spam) and "probability" (confidence score)

Handles empty messages with proper HTTP error

⿦ Streamlit Frontend

Interactive web app

Users input SMS in a textbox and click Predict

Connects to FastAPI backend for real-time prediction

Displays:

Green message if Ham

Red message if Spam

Confidence score

Technologies Used

Python

Data Processing: Pandas, NumPy

Text Processing: NLTK (tokenization, stopwords, stemming)

Machine Learning: Scikit-learn (MultinomialNB, TF-IDF, GridSearchCV)

Visualization: Matplotlib, Seaborn, WordCloud

API: FastAPI

Frontend: Streamlit

Serialization & Model Tracking: Joblib, MLflow

